name: Christiana Velis
bio:
Christiana Velis is a trusted clinical nutritionist based in the heart of Sydney, specialising in digestive health, women’s wellness, and hormones health. Christiana combines scientific knowledge with a compassionate, client-centred approach, offering a path to wellbeing that respects your pace and personal needs.

Christiana’s passion is to unravel the tangle of hormonal imbalances and impaired gut health, which can lead to increased PMS, mood shifts, fatigue, nutrient deficiency, and chronic disease. Christiana aims to help clients discover how these issues intertwine, and can be improved through diet and lifestyle changes. Christiana aims to make her clients feel heard, understood, and empowered to make the choices that align best with their wellbeing.

Before Christiana became a nutritionist she was a corporate lawyer. She is also a trained yoga teacher and a mum of two young kiddies.
teacher_quote: Guiding you through a deeper level of well-being through science-based nutrition and wellness approaches

name: Tara O
bio:
Tara O is incredibly passionate about helping women transform their sex lives. A sex coach, writer, speaker and sexual empowerment entrepreneur, she believes that true health and happiness come from complete wholeness, accepting every part of yourself including your authentic sexuality.

When Tara isn’t teaching women how to experience life-changing pleasure, she can be found covered in kids, Weet-bix or her husband.
teacher_quote: Helping Women Get The Pleasure They Deserve!

name: Linia Patel
bio: With PhD in Public health and over 100 published articles on diet and health, Linia has a strong grounding in nutrition science. Yet she combines this with with her passion of translating science into easy-to-digest and practical advice which is why she is also often seen as a nutrition expert in the media. She is a British Dietetic Association Spokesperson and is regularly seen appearing on national TV and being quoted in the press. She is particularly passionate about women’s health and spends her clinical time working with women (athletes, non-athletes and everything in between).
teacher_quote: Helping you to understand how your body works and how to become the best version of yourself

name: Elle Brown
bio: Elle Brown is a Women's wellness nutritionist, specialising in female fatigue, hormone health, emotional health and eating behaviours; binge eating and body system balance.  With 10 years experience working in the health space, Elle is passionate about education and empowerment. Known for unearthing the root cause, finding the 'why' and implementing attainable and practical strategies, Elle works closely with her clients to feel supported, heard and encouraged on their journey to health and wellness.  Elle endeavours to impart that food is not simply for fuel and often shares the importance of 'joy' within food choices; for health, happiness and energy! Elle has completed a Bachelor of Health Science in Nutrition and Dietetic Medicine and a Masters at Deakin University in Human Nutrition and Research. Forever committed to continual learning, Elle has completed further study in the emotional body and binge eating space and is a chai, chocolate and peanut butter enthusiast; feeling most at home by the ocean.
teacher_quote: Providing gentle, supportive and nourishing care to Women on their healing journey.

name: Hannah Korrel
bio: Dr Korrel is an expert in the field of neuroscience and will take us on a fascinating journey through the world of mental health and its neurological basis. Author and Neuropsychologist, Dr. Korrel has spent over a decade becoming an expert on why the brain makes us do the things we do. A fierce mental health advocate, Hannah brings neurology and psychology together to explain common life dilemmas. Hannah is both a Clinical Neuropsychologist, Neuroscientist, Psychologist and author. She has worked in hospitals around Australia and currently heads up the neuropsychology service of a major hospital in Sydney. She has a neuropsychology practice in Sydney where she has helped people get the best out of their IQ by diagnosing cognitive strengths and overcoming things like ADHD, attention issues and autism. Dr Korrel regularly appeared on programs like The Project, The Today Show, and ABC radio to bring Australia easy-to-understand neuropsych tips for improving mental health and IQ.
teacher_quote: Neuropsychologist, Author, PhD Neuroscience

name: Miranda Cheng
bio:
Holistic Pelvic Care Practitionare | Intimacy, pleasure & Sex (Re)Education Facilitator

Approaching a decade of on going studies, practice and facilitation I have been privileged to learn from the world’s leading somatic and embodiment teachers. My passion for working in the field of Holistic Pelvic Care™ and The Fembodiment Method™ continues to propel me into garnering a deeper understanding of the feminine landscape.

My greatest wish is to empower you with healing practices which bring you into a deeper connection with your femininity. To bless you with freedom, joy and the pleasure of living in confidence, radiance and feeling embodied in your true authentic self. To reclaim your pleasure as yours, understand that it is your birth rite and to expand it exponentially.
teacher_quote: Pelvic care intimacy, pleasure & sex (re)education

name: Steph Wall
bio: Steph has a passion for facilitating a space for students to deepen into the complexities of life through the tradition of yoga. Deeply devoted to self-discovery and engaging in the creative unfolding of life, it is clear that Steph's intention with the yoga path is to stay awake and aware during the transformational process of Life.
teacher_quote: “Whenever you find yourself on the side of the majority, it’s time to pause and reflect” - Mark Twain

name: Alice Browning
bio:
Founder of The Fold, Yogi, Writer and Mother.

I guide shapes, asanas, poses and sitting deeply in the now. Teaching full time for over a decade, the way in which I hold space for my students is unhurried, steady, strong and supportive, with a big old dose of realness. A dance Instructor, before I found my mat, teaching is like breathing, to me. Adding to my initial 500 hour TT by attending workshops, masterclasses and advanced training with the likes of Kathryn Budig, Patrick Beach, Shiva Rea and Sarah Powers over the years has aided me in developing my own distinct style.

These days, I can be found splitting my time between my little flower Dahlia, teaching in- studio and online. Always with an almond latte in hand, manifesting my dream home in the country with a wrap-around verandah, a place where neighbours are a distant memory.
teacher_quote: Founder of The Fold, Yogi, Writer and most importantly, Mother. I guide shapes, asanas, poses and sitting deeply in the now.

name: Alex Farner
bio:
Offered as an evolving practice that grows with you, Alex's classes weave an intelligent blend of yoga, pelvic floor mobility, meridian theory and myofascial release to bolster fertility, strong and healthy pregnancies, restful and empowered postnatal support.

Feathered with breathwork, anatomical education and tools to promote calm and a regulated nervous system, this proven method is designed uniquely to support women and have resounding effects on future generations. Bridging the gap between holistic practices and the medical system, Alex cultivates knowlege to educate and empower women with awareness to enhance our experience of life.

Alex is Vinyasa and Yin trained (500+ hours), with specialities in prenatal and postnatal yoga, female health yoga and cycle support.
teacher_quote: Purpose built practices to support female vitality, prenatal and postnatal growth.

name: Janet Gooding
bio: Mom, Yogi, Teacher, Business Owner ~ I am a yoga teacher, retreat facilitator, and forever student. I love all things yoga and people and believe life is easier if you simply slow down. As an 800hr Experienced Registered Yoga Teacher, I aim to lead classes that are inclusive, inventive and inspiring. You can expect alignment-based flows and nourishing yin practices infused with relatable wisdom from my experience as a yogi, teacher and now mama. And sometimes I dose out a bit of tough love! My hope is for you to love yourself where you are at and empower you to make the changes you want to live your most aligned and vibrant life. When I’m not hanging out with my daughter Gigi and Labrador Tony, you can find me leading yoga retreats all over the world. From my love of yoga, people and travel, I co-founded Nectar, an international yoga retreats company. I love witnessing students rediscover their zest for life through travel and yoga. I can’t wait to connect with you on and off the mat!
teacher_quote: My hope is for you to love yourself where you are at and empower you to make the changes you want to live your most aligned and vibrant life.

name: Jacklyn Carlson
bio: A Mama of two, dedicated Motherhood & Parent Coach and Breathwork Instructor. My passion lies in connecting and guiding them through the transformative journey of motherhood. I’m a catalyst for change, ready to support you on the path to self-discovery, providing spaces where women can reconnect with themselves, their bodies and their children. I offer services encompassing 1:1 coaching, online parenting courses, group programs, breathwork events, community workshops, Circle of Security programs and more.
teacher_quote: Support for mums, made simple

name: Jennifer Ward
bio:
Understanding just how powerful the female body is has given me an even greater respect for women going through their own journey to motherhood and a burning desire to make their experience as positive as possible.

My journey into naturally caring for the woman has led me to completing a Masters in Reproductive Medicine which is helping me bridge the gap between the medical world and allied care. 

Over the last 10 years I have helped 1000’s of woman on their journey to balanced hormones and motherhood.
teacher_quote: I help women make sense of and improve their hormones before, during and after pregnancy

name: Emma Berry
bio:
As a mama-to-be and women’s health osteopath, Emma has a strong focus on pelvic pain, pregnancy, postpartum and pelvic floor health.  Emma strives to provide holistic, nurturing and individualised health care to women of all life stages. Her goal is to empower women to respect and better understand their bodies.

Her personal experience with endometriosis, infertility and chronic pain fuels her interest in this field, understanding first-hand the profound impact these conditions can have on someone's life. 

She cherishes the opportunity to support women through their fertility, pregnancy, or postpartum journey. Her areas of interest include pregnancy, birth preparation, postpartum care, endometriosis management, pelvic floor dysfunction, caesarean & perineal scar tissue release, nervous system support, and chronic pelvic pain. Emma has pursued advanced studies with leading Australian osteopaths in women’s pelvic health and pelvic floor rehabilitation, ensuring comprehensive care for her patients throughout menstruation, motherhood and menopause.
teacher_quote: Providing education and holistic, nurturing & individualized healthcare to people throughout all stages of life

name: Samantha Flook
bio:
My sessions focus on a practical approach to therapy. Helping you understand yourself and address issues by identifying and altering patterns in your behaviour, through strategic tools & techniques. I focus on teaching you “how” to manage experiences rather than avoiding them, guiding you to move from your current state to your desired state. This includes learning “how to”:

- Express your needs and feelings
- Turn avoidance into action
- Reconnect with your body and make beneficial decisions for your health & wellbeing
- Build boundaries in relationships

Using mindfulness, strategic psychotherapy, clinical hypnotherapy, and cognitive coaching tools, I aim to empower you to make and sustain positive changes, fostering self-confidence, independence, and effectiveness in all areas of your life.
teacher_quote: Teaching you to regulate your emotions, turn self doubt into self confidence & create behaviours that serve you.

name: Erin Brooks
bio: Hi, I'm Erin Brooks, a Pilates teacher based in Manly, Australia. I love putting a fresh spin on classic Pilates moves to make your workout dynamic, challenging and fun. While I keep things interesting, I always maintain a strong focus on proper form to help you get the most out of each movement. My carefully planned classes guarantee you'll leave feeling worked out and energized. Whether you're new to Pilates or a seasoned pro, I'd love to help you strengthen your body and discover what it can do!
teacher_quote: PILATES INSTRUCTOR & CO-FOUNDER

name: Sally Jane Douglas
bio:
Sally Jane Douglas is a passionate women's life mastery mentor supporting women to feel deeply, live fearlessly, and love wholeheartedly.

With 17 years of experience in women's empowerment and development, Sally is devoted to supporting women to overcome self-doubt and self-abandonment so they can beam with confidence and trust themselves and their decisions impeccably. Her sweet-spot is guiding women to attune with themselves and intuition to embody self-belief and emotional resilience.

Through private mentoring and Uniquely YOU Academy, Sally compassionately guides women to connect with and live aligned to their authentic truth.
teacher_quote: feel deeply • live fearlessly • love wholeheartedly

name: Jenna McDonald
bio:
Jenna McDonald is a leading fertility acupuncturist and the founder of The Fertility Suite in Manly. With a Master’s degree in Reproductive Medicine, she specializes in supporting individuals and couples through natural conception, IVF, and egg freezing preparation. Jenna is passionate about evidence-based care and helping people optimize their reproductive health.

With years of clinical experience, she understands the importance of preparing both eggs and sperm for the best possible outcomes. Her holistic approach combines acupuncture, nutrition, and lifestyle strategies to support those navigating their fertility journey.

Jenna regularly collaborates with fertility specialists and IVF clinics, including Monash IVF, to provide integrative care. She is dedicated to educating both patients and practitioners on the crucial role of preparation in egg freezing and reproductive health
teacher_quote: I am equipped with the knowledge, scientific research and the true motivation to help you maximise your fertility.

name: Jordanna Levin
bio:
Hi, I’m Jordanna Levin and I wrote a few books you might dig, host a handful of successful podcast shows, and consider myself a keeping-it-real astrologer #toottoot (that’s me tooting my own horn).

If you’d like to judge me by my star sign, I’m a double gemini with a virgo moon (I know, it’s a lot!), but please don’t put me in a box and label me ‘woo woo’ (or two-faced, I know what they say about Geminis).

My background is journalism which means I’ve got a talent for taking topics that are deemed too ‘big’, too ‘spiritual’ or too ’dry’ and flipping them on their head, making them relatable, witty and often a lil bit sexy (can’t help it, natural talent). I believe ah-ha moments are contagious and that self-awareness is your greatest superpower.

I currently write and record from the sunny coastal town of Byron Bay.
teacher_quote: Astrologer & Writer

name: Amelia Hetherington
bio:
Amelia is a Clinical Naturopath with a Bachelor in Health Science (Naturopathy), with extra training in Live Blood Analysis and Emotional Freedom Technique (EFT Tapping).
Amelia has a true passion for supporting her clients and their families through periods of ill-health. Amelia aims to facilitate clients to tune into their highest frequency and return home to their better selves.
Her passion is to help each patient feel empowered, conscious and balanced, all while providing gentle and professional treatment every step of the way.

Amelia integrates science into her practise with the use of both functional testing methods (DUTCH hormone panel, Complete Digestive Stool Analysis, Adrenocortex Stress Profile, Heavy Metal Testing) and the study of pathology (blood pathology) to find the root cause of illnesses and address them.
With this knowledge, Amelia aims to encourage wellness and the natural mechanisms of the body in a process of healing with the use of nutraceutical supplements, herbal tinctures and dietary/lifestyle changes based on testing results. Amelia has a strong passion for gastrointestinal health, mental health and female reproductive conditions.
Amelia is truly driven by her patient's success and enjoys curated individualised plans and workshops to share the joy and radiance with all.
teacher_quote: Supporting you to walk in alignment with your best self, synergistically with nature.

name: Caterina Boutagy
bio:
Caterina is a yoga teacher, pilates instructor, retreat facilitator, and Ayurvedic wellness coach. She is deeply in love with the complex and rich teachings of yoga, classical tantra, and Ayurveda and considers it a great privilege to practice and share these traditions.

With over 1,000 hours of training and 10 years of teaching under her belt, Cat loves creating badass and creative sequences shared with her whole heart. Based in the hinterland of Byron where she grew up, Cat devotes most of her spare time to her garden, dancing around her living room to deep bassy tunes, and lounging on the beach.
teacher_quote: "The Western idea of practice is to acquire a skill. The Eastern idea of practice on the other hand, is to create the person, or rather, to reveal the complete person who is already there." - Stephen Nachmanovitch

name: Eliza Giles
bio:
Spending over half her life immersed in these ancient technologies and teachings Eliza is an eternal student and practitioner who thrives in the expression and celebration of life and these sacred pathways of Truth.

A practitioner of the yogic technologies for the last 20 years she has traveled across the globe to study the yogic systems with modern and traditional masters of many linages and teachings. She has been sharing these teachings internationally as a facilitator for the last 13 years.

She has trained with meditation masters, tantric leaders, Sanskrit scholars yoga masters and leading teachers across the continents, holding influences from her teachers Yoga Rupa Rod Stryker, Dr Lorin Roache, Sally Kempton, Tiffany Cruikshank, Jo Phee and more.
teacher_quote: Weaving Ancient Traditions into Modern Transformation

name: Hannah Crerar
bio: Hannah is passionate about the body-mind-soul connection. She offers a modern approach to self discovery and loves to share the convergence between spirituality and science. She has a background in Law and Commerce, with 4 years experience in the corporate world. Her interest in holistic wellness inspired her to leave her corporate role in 2016, to volunteer at an Australian health retreat and later pursue Psychology studies in her home country, New Zealand. Hannah’s yoga practice plays a significant role in her life’s journey. She first stepped on a yoga mat at age 16 and credits the teachings to fast tracking her own self-growth and self-compassion. At age 23 she became a registered Yoga teacher and has completed multiple teacher-trainings worldwide. Hannah’s innate curiosity and intuition-led lifestyle means she is continually immersing herself in all things body-mind-soul. Her strong spiritual practice is complemented by a solid understanding of the science behind why it all works. Self-love begins with self-awareness and Hannah is on a mission to bring a greater sense of awareness to as many people as possible. Her offerings focus on the deeper layers of self, combining modern understandings of the human psyche alongside knowledge of ancient wisdom traditions. Her work empowers and liberates people with self-awareness tools to create a life in alignment with their authentic self.
teacher_quote: Self-awareness is one of the greatest gifts we can give ourselves as our Soul’s evolve.

name: Jo Lincolne
bio: As a woman with endo herself, Jo set out to heal herself naturally when she was diagnosed, as there were not many answers that doctors were able to give her or effective medical treatments. This has led her to right where she is today – helping women holistically find relief, hope, vitality and the power to control their health again. Jo Lincolne is a certified holistic wellness coach for endometriosis and has been practicing for over 10 years. As an Endometriosis Wellness Specialist and educator, Jo provides natural endometriosis support and education to help women heal and manage their endo-symptoms. You can connect with Jo on FB and IG @jolincolnewellness as she shares current research, natural therapies, tips and practices for living and healing with endometriosis. You can also find her on her website jolincolnewellness.com which is a hub of endo-info, and she’s recently been interviewed in a 2-part series on the podcast ‘In Her Flow’.
teacher_quote: Take back control of your health & heal. Learn to understand what your body is telling you.

name: Ruby Josif
bio: Ruby Josif, is a Certified Holistic Sex Coach, Feminine Embodiment Practitioner, and a Certified Therapeutic Yoni Massage Practitioner. Working with women one-on-one, couples and with groups, she combines her diverse training in sexology, Neo-tantra, embodiment and the erotic arts to provide her clients with an integrated approach to sexual healing and regaining their erotic spark. Ruby specialises in gently guiding her clients to overcome sexual challenges, connect with their unique feminine essence, understand the truth of their body and pleasure and feel confident in communicating their authentic needs, desires and boundaries. Whether it’s through coaching and mentorship or Therapeutic Yoni Massage, Ruby invites her clients to strip away the deep layers of subconscious patterning, behaviours and conditioning so they can learn how to express and enjoy their authentic sexual nature and create a more passionate, sustainable and fullingfilling sex life.
teacher_quote: Creating a space where her clients feel safe to discover the truth of who they are as sexual beings

name: Pascale Falempin Arcadi
bio: I am a certified Pilates instructor with hours of specialised training and 10 years of teaching in various settings. Movement of some sort has always been present in my life. From intense, tireless movement during the years I trained as a dancer, to very basic movement in the years that followed my quitting ballet to switch paths completely and start studying/working. Yet movement was a constant, and it's always guided me both physically and mentally. I have worked in studio as well as corporate settings, with groups and on a one to one basis. Training with me means you'll be seen, challenged, heard and accompanied every step of the way as creating a connection with you is what passionates me the most.
teacher_quote: Your body is the only place you have to live in

name: Sarina Coventry
bio: Sarina Coventry is a degree qualified nutritionist (BHSc) and EFT Tapping Practitioner. She takes a holistic approach that seeks to educate and empower women toward working WITH their bodies rather than against them. Through 1:1 online sessions, she teaches women how to have happy hormones, support their nervous system and process negative beliefs related to food, themselves and their body.
teacher_quote: Unlock the power of working WITH your body rather than AGAINST it.

name: Monique Cormack
bio:
I am a qualified nutritionist, holding a Bachelor of Health Science (Nutritional and Dietetic Medicine). My role is to help you reach your health goals by assessing your diet and lifestyle and working with you to address any issues we identify.
Being nourished is about more than just what you put on your plate. I look not only at what you eat, but how you eat and how you live, and help optimise your health.

Prior to studying nutrition, I was a stressed-out corporate lawyer, struggling with disordered eating. I was confused by the mixed messages about food and diets constantly thrown about in popular media. I chose to change my life and study nutrition so I could cut through the rubbish and learn how to really eat well.
My journey into specialising in women’s health and fertility has been very much influenced by my own experience with infertility. I struggled with disordered eating and experienced extended hypothalamic amenorrhea after coming off the Pill, eventually going through ovulation induction and IVF. I truly understand and empathise with the impact that infertility can have.
teacher_quote: As an accredited nutritionist my goal is to equip you with the knowledge and tools to truly improve your health for the long term.

name: Kate Joy
bio:
She believes in Meditation that doesn’t play by the rules and desires for herself and supports others on a more easeful, graceful and ethical journey through life via her meditation teachings.

Recently she has brought Cyclic Meditations to the platform, another way to deepen your relationship to your body and harness into the potency of cyclical living and on the way are more practices focused on varying qualities of meditation.

A fan of her pooch Roo, pancakes and keeping it real, we cannot wait to welcome more from Kate as we continue to grow.
teacher_quote: Learn to give yourself time, to pause and breathe

name: Amy Baxter
bio:
Amy is the co-founder of Nectar, Yoga Teacher, traveller, lover of life, forever student and life learner. Amy began her love for movement at the age of 4 taking up dance class where she grew up in NSW, Australia. This passion later grew into a career in performing arts. Throughout her performing career she dipped in and out of yoga as part of her rehab program whilst recovering from injury. It wasn't until 2014 when visiting Ubud, Bali that she felt a deep love and connection to yoga and wanted to deepen her personal practice and begin her yoga teacher training journey.

Amy trained under Annie Carpenter and completed Annie's 200hr Yoga Teacher Training in SmartFLOW. Upon completion of the training, Amy felt a deep connection to the practice which grew into teaching yoga full time in Sydney. In 2019 Amy moved to London to pursue her career and love for travel. With teaching experience spanning across Australia, Europe & UK she has led Teacher Training Programs, completed 50hr Comprehensive Anatomy Course under David Keil, 30hr Yin intensive with Norman Blair & currently training in Crystal Bowl Sound Healing.

Amy's teaching style is known for its precision and playfulness. Her classes will make you 'work' yet embrace adventure on your mat. Through intelligent sequencing and fluid transitions her classes calm the mind and bring you to the present moment. Expect to be challenged, yet nurtured in an inclusive space where you can freely explore your fullest potential.
teacher_quote: Your yoga mat is like your safe island, a little oasis that can bring you back to yourself. Offering your body & mind freedom to explore.

name: Vee
bio: I'm Vee, coming from France where I spent the first 22 years of my life before moving to Barcelona and now; Sydney. My favourite days are always filled with movement, coffee in the sunshine, ocean dip and chocolate based treats! I am teaching yoga exactly how I live my life: giving everything I have from the bottom of my heart, with love. I am willing to make sure students feel at ease when they step into my class, I want to give back what I have received from my own experience as a student, especially when I first started yoga: I have always been welcomed with big open arms and warm smiles. I am trained in Vinyasa, Yin Yoga & Pilates. My yoga classes are built around a flow, a deep connection between breath and movement. I am passionate about creating classes around a strong theme. I like to look at yoga as a gracious dance between movement and breath, inhale and exhale. Depending on the class style, I adapt the pace, the intensity but there are 2 components that you can almost always find: pranayama to start with to settle and get grounded and a meditation/relaxation to unwind and receive the benefits of the practice at the end of class. My pilates classes are slow, steady and are meant to balance out the entire body. We take our time to build the principles so we move with complete awareness, build strength and confidence from the inside.
teacher_quote: I teach exactly how I live my life: giving everything I have from the bottom of my heart, with love.
